I've taken CS 70 and currently taking 165. They are completely different classes.... I found there are ~20% overlap between 70 (edit: Data 100) and 165.

Please do not modify my answer if you don't fully understand what I meant to say. There is no overlap (i.e. 0%) between 70 and 165. 165 teaches some methods to model the data sets, which are partially covered in Data 100 (such as Cross-Validation and Bias-Variance Tradeoff)
